Fixed drug eruptions have occurred with tetracycline and have been associated with worsening severity upon subsequent administrations, including generalized bullous fixed drug eruption (see 
                        ADVERSE REACTIONS
                     ). If severe skin reactions occur, discontinue tetracycline hydrochloride capsules immediately and institute appropriate therapy.

